<br>
A friend of mine came over while I was playing EQ and asked if he could play.  I said sure, he created a new charector and set out into the mean harsh world.  All of a sudden this guy who is new as well starts trailing him.  Walking everywhere he went and ignoring all comments made to him.  My friend is absolutly distraught.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why is this guy following me?&quot;<br>
&quot;Do people follow you in this game?&quot;<br>
&quot;Has this ever happened to you?&quot;<br>
&quot;What should I do?&quot;<br>
&quot;Can I tell that gaurd he's following me?&quot;<br>
<br>
I was in tears!  So I decided to try and duplicate the experiment.  I introduced into the world a charming little guy by the name of Pucslappa!  (Yes, Im a hockey fan.)  I followed the first person I saw for about 3 minutes before he noticed me.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Hail Pucslappa!&quot;<br>
. . . no reply<br>
&quot;Hail Pucslappa!&quot;<br>
. . . no reply<br>
<br>
So he takes off again and I trail him.  He runs in and out of several building attempting to shake me.  Soon he stops turns around and hails me again, no answer.  I start getting tells asking if I'm following him.  You'd think that me being his shadow for the last 8 1/2 minutes might tip him off but he runs away again after no reply.  <br>
<br>
Finally he runs up to a druid and begs for SoW because &quot;I'm being followed.&quot;  The druid appropriatly responds &quot;? ? ?&quot;  Regardless, the druid casts SoW on him and I send a tell to the druid and say that I'm with him and I'm being followed as well.  The druid /em grins and shakes his head and casts SoW.  I trail this guy out of the city into the newbie area, he turns to me and waves and begins running at SoW speed.  He runs for a minute and turns around to find me still right behind him.<br>
<br>
He finally (and this was all I was waiting for) says to me;  Would you stop following me?  I send him a tell and inform him it was a joke and what had happened to my friend and he was really cool about it, we had a good laugh.  He told me he responded the same way my friend did.  &quot;I couldn't figure out what was going on.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> So</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, the moral of this story is:<br>
<br>
